00:58:53.240 --> 00:58:53.920
Oh.

00:59:02.320 --> 00:59:07.040
- Today we filmed queue 1, scene 1. / - Scene 1.

00:59:07.040 --> 00:59:09.200
- And it went surprisingly well. / - True.

00:59:09.200 --> 00:59:13.840
Nothing got stuck. The acting rhythm was super smooth. We all gossip too much.

00:59:26.920 --> 00:59:29.640
A new morning after we leave Mom behind.

00:59:29.640 --> 00:59:36.000
Then when we came downstairs, we saw Nany Yam and P’Sin whispering about something.

00:59:36.000 --> 00:59:37.440
So I was like, huh?

00:59:37.880 --> 00:59:43.800
Something seemed off. Because Khun Yai is sick. he used his powers.

00:59:44.040 --> 00:59:49.080
And when he uses his power, he becomes translucent. When he’s like that, he can’t meet people.

00:59:49.440 --> 00:59:53.240
I also wondered where he had gone.

00:59:53.240 --> 01:00:00.560
And then I saw that Khun Yai used up more power fighting.

01:00:04.520 --> 01:00:09.320
They said we’d be filming inside a secret tunnel that was pretty narrow.

01:00:09.320 --> 01:00:11.480
I didn’t think it would be this narrow.

01:00:11.960 --> 01:00:14.960
It’s so tight that you have to walk single file inside.

01:00:14.960 --> 01:00:17.800
With just one camera set up, it almost filled the whole frame.

01:00:17.800 --> 01:00:22.480
I don’t know why Khun Yai likes this place so much. There are plenty of better ones.

01:00:22.760 --> 01:00:25.040
Oh right! he’s a ghost. He has to hide from Kaewta. Makes sense.

01:00:25.040 --> 01:00:27.760
His power’s weak lately too. We need to make a lot of merit for him.

01:00:34.160 --> 01:00:39.280
This is a prop, okay? Not real.

01:00:39.960 --> 01:00:43.280
That’s why the sound it makes is like…

01:00:54.280 --> 01:00:55.920
Stop, it’s making my teeth hurt.

